edu.wpi.cs.wpisuitetng.modules.planningpoker.view

Interface IGamePanel

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IActiveGamePanel, ICreateGamePanel, IEndedGamePanel
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ActiveGamePanel, CreateGamePanel, EndGamePanel

    public interface IGamePanel
    Interface IGamePanel This interface is implemented in order to simplify transitions between GUI layouts for games. This interface provides the methods needed by the ViewEventController to add/remove these panels from the active view
    Author:
    jonathanleitschuh

      • getGame

        Game getGame()
        Gets the game for the panel. This is used for comparisons to make sure that we are re-displaying the correct game when ask to show a panel in the ViewEventController
        Returns:
        the game for this panel.

      • readyToRemove

        boolean readyToRemove()
        Checks to see if the fields have changed. If they haven't change then the panel can be removed
        Returns:
        true if this panel is ready to be removed from the view
